# Kai Asset Forge — AI Coding Rules

You are inside Kai Asset Forge, Popo's autonomous pixel art factory.

## Project
- Root: C:\Users\khair\Kai-Asset-Forge
- Pipeline: Scout → Forge → Curator → Packager → Lister
- Gold standard: 0x72 Dungeon Tileset II v1.7

## Pixel Art Quality
- Generate sprites ONLY via: `python aseprite-forge.py --character <name>`
- 16 character templates: dwarf, elf, wizard, orc, knight, angel, pumpkin, skeleton, goblin, imp, demon, ogre, zombie, lizard, chort, wogol
- 30 dungeon tiles: `python aseprite-forge.py --tiles`
- 24-color dungeon palette (hue-shifted, never grey shadows)
- 1px external outline only
- idle×4 + walk×4 + hit×1 per character
- Verify: `ls forge-output/ && file forge-output/*/*.png`

## Workflow
1. Build → git add -A → git commit → git push (every step)
2. Execute full plans without pausing
3. Verify files on disk before reporting
4. "now what?" = pick most critical action, execute now. No menus.

## Agents (Hermes Profiles)
- scout — Elf archer, market research
- forge — Dwarf smith, sprite generation (aseprite-forge.py)
- curator — Knight, quality inspection
- packager — Goblin, bundle assembly
- lister — Elf merchant, marketplace listings

## Tools
- Aseprite CLI: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Aseprite\Aseprite.exe
- Dashboard: http://localhost:3004/factory (Hermes OS v5)
- Hermes: hermes CLI with profiles
